description:
Bug 38131ajc needs -d option. I am using 1.1rc1. This is a regression since rc1 and a deviation from javac. I am guessing this may have something to do with a change in the underlying Eclipse compiler.

To reproduce the issue:
1. Create a class in a subpackage such as:
   package subpackage;
   public class Test {
       public static void main(String[] args) {
           System.out.println("Hello");
       }
   }
2. Compile using the following command: ajc -d subpackage subpackage\Test.java

Currently, a directory named "subpackage" is created under the existing "subpackage" directory when using ajc command. However, with javac command, this behavior does not occur.

Expected behavior:
When compiling with ajc command, the same behavior as javac command should be observed. No additional "subpackage" directory should be created.
